"text":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"SRV (service) records are used by some network protocols to provide","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"service-specific aliasing and load-balancing. For example, XMPP","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(Jabber) uses SRV records to locate the XMPP server for a domain;"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"rather than connecting directly to ‘example.com’ or assuming a"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"specific server hostname like ‘xmpp.example.com’, an XMPP client"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"would look up the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"xmpp-client"},{"text":" SRV record for ‘example.com’, and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"then connect to whatever host was pointed to by that record."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Resolver.lookup_service"},{"type":"text","text":"] or"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"Gio.Resolver.lookup_service_async","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] to find the "},{"code":"GSrvTarget","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for a given service. However, if you are simply planning to connect","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the remote service, you can use [class"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/NetworkService","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"]’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[iface"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/SocketConnectable","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"] interface and not need to worry about"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GSrvTarget"},{"text":" at all.","type":"tex